body:
I was [comparing Yosys against ISE and Vivado](https://github.com/rodrigomelo9/yosys-versus), using examples provided by Xilinx. After discarding some files with errors (a `.v` which is in fact a `.zip`, another one which is VHDL package with stranger things, etc), I found a few problems. Here one of them.

## Steps to reproduce the issue

The conflicted file:

```
// A function that computes and returns a constant value
//
// functions_constant.v
//
module functions_constant (clk, we, a, di, do);
    parameter ADDRWIDTH = 8;
    parameter DATAWIDTH = 4;
    input clk;
    input we;
    input  [ADDRWIDTH-1:0] a;
    input  [DATAWIDTH-1:0] di;
    output [DATAWIDTH-1:0] do;

    function integer getSize;
        input addrwidth;
        begin
            getSize = 2**addrwidth;
        end
    endfunction

    reg [DATAWIDTH-1:0] ram [getSize(ADDRWIDTH)-1:0];

    always @(posedge clk) begin
        if (we)
            ram[a] <= di;
    end
    assign do = ram[a];

endmodule
```

The Yosys command to reproduce the problem and the message:

```
$ yosys -Q -p "read_verilog examples/vivado/functions_constant.v"

-- Running command `read_verilog examples/vivado/functions_constant.v' --

1. Executing Verilog-2005 frontend: examples/vivado/functions_constant.v
Parsing Verilog input from `examples/vivado/functions_constant.v' to AST representation.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\functions_constant'.
examples/vivado/functions_constant.v:21: ERROR: Memory `\ram' with non-constant width or size!
```

It complains about `reg [DATAWIDTH-1:0] ram [getSize(ADDRWIDTH)-1:0];`, but `getSize` returns a constant value. I used this kind of solutions in some VHDL memories that I have, and I think that it is a desired feature to support.

I can create and provide another example if needed (to avoid to include a Xilinx example in the repository).

